0dad%2C%20who%20leads%20their%20senior%20division%2C%20works%20with%20those%20clients'%20parents%2C%20figuratively%20and%2C%20in%20some%20cases%2C%20literally.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20a%20litmus%20test%3A%20%3Cem%3EIf%3C%2Fem%3E%20an%20older%20person%20planned%20their%20finances%20well%2C%20is%20financially%20independent%2C%20has%20enough%20income%20to%20support%20their%20needs%20and%20is%20not%20in%20danger%20of%20running%20out%2C%20and%20wants%20to%20pass%20down%20money%20to%20their%20kids%2C%20then%20it%20can%20be%20a%20good%20idea%20to%20do%20it%20sooner%20rather%20than%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20consider%20inheritances%20and%20money%20from%20families%20a%20gift%20of%20love%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20your%20intention%20is%20to%20give%20that%20money%20to%20family%20as%20an%20inheritance%2C%20you%20probably%20want%20that%20money%20put%20to%20best%20use%20for%20the%20maximum%20amount%20of%20time%20that%20creates%20the%20most%20peace%20of%20mind%20for%20everybody%20involved.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20max%20amount%20that%20can%20be%20gifted%20each%20year%20tax-free%20is%20%2418%2C000%20for%20an%20individual%20or%20%2436%2C000%20for%20a%20couple.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDrucker%20said%20he%20thinks%20he's%20seeing%20this%20wealth%20transfer%20happen%20more%20often%20in%20part%20because%20the%20current%20estate%20tax%20exemption%20put%20in%20place%20by%20the%20Tax%20Cuts%20and%20Jobs%20Act%20of%202017%20is%20set%20to%20expire%20at%20the%20end%20of%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20federal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpersonal-finance%2Fwhat-is-estate-tax%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eestate%20tax%3C%2Fa%3E%20currently%20ranges%20from%2018%25%20to%2040%25%20and%20kicks%20in%20for%20assets%20passed%20on%20that%20are%20above%20%2413.61%20million.%20That%20threshold%3Cstrong%3E%20%3C%2Fstrong%3Ecould%20be%20cut%20in%20half%20in%202026%2C%20meaning%20the%20estate%20tax%20would%20apply%20to%20more%20families.%