oe%20Biden's%20natural%20successor%20if%20he%20bowed%20to%20growing%20pressure%20and%20stepped%20aside%20as%20the%20Democratic%20candidate%20in%20the%202024%20election%2C%20top%20Democrats%20say.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENow%20party%20donors%2C%20activists%20and%20officials%20are%20asking%3A%20Does%20she%20have%20a%20better%20chance%20than%20Biden%20of%20beating%20Donald%20Trump%3F%20Biden%20is%20staying%20in%20the%20race%2C%20he%20has%20said%20repeatedly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHarris%2C%2059%2C%20a%20former%20U.S.%20senator%20and%20California%20attorney%20general%2C%20would%20be%20the%20first%20woman%20to%20become%20president%20of%20the%20United%20States%20if%20she%20were%20the%20party's%20nominee%20and%20prevailed%20in%20the%20Nov.%205%20election.%20She%20is%20the%20first%20African%20American%20and%20Asian%20person%20to%20serve%20as%20vice%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHer%20three-and-a-half-year%20White%20House%20tenure%20has%20been%20characterized%20by%20a%20lackluster%20start%2C%20staff%20turnover%2C%20and%20early%20policy%20portfolios%20including%20migration%20from%20Central%20America%20that%20did%20not%20produce%20major%20successes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20recently%20as%20last%20year%2C%20many%20inside%20the%20White%20House%20and%20the%20Biden%20campaign%20team%20privately%20worried%20Harris%20was%20a%20liability%20for%20the%20campaign.%20The%20situation%20has%20changed%20significantly%20since%20then%2C%20Democratic%20officials%20have%20said%2C%20as%20she%20stepped%20forward%20on%20abortion%20rights%20and%20courted%20young%20voters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ESome%20Polls%20Favour%20Harris%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecent%20polls%20suggest%20Harris%20could%20do%20better%20than%20Biden%20against%20Trump%2C%20the%20Republican%20candidate%2C%20although%20she%20would%20face%20a%20tight%20contest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20CNN%20poll%20released%20on%20July%202%20found%20voters%20favor%20Trump%20over%20Biden%20by%20six%20percentage%20points%2C%2049%25%20to%2043%25.%20Harris%20also%20trailed%20Trump%2C%2047%25%20to%2045%25%2C%20within%20the%20margin%20of%20error.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20found%20independents%20back%20Harris%2043%25-40%25%20over%20Trump%2C%20and%20moderate%20voters%20of%20both%20parties%20prefer%20her%2051-39%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20Reuters%2FIpsos%20poll%20after%20last%20week's%20televised%20debate%20between%20Trump%20and%20a%20faltering%20Biden%20found%20Harris%20and%20Trump%20were%20nearly%20tied%2C%20with%2042%25%20supporting%20her%20and%2043%25%20backing%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnly%20former%20first%20lady%20Michelle%20Obama%2C%20who%20has%20never%20expressed%20any%20interest%20in%20getting%20into%20the%20race%2C%20polled%20higher%20among%20possible%20alternatives%20to%20Biden.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInternal%20polling%20shared%20by%20the%20Biden%20campaign%20after%20the%20debate%20shows%20Harris%20with%20the%20same%20odds%20as%20Biden%20of%20beating%20Trump%2C%20with%2045%25%20of%20voters%20saying%20they%20would%20vote%20for%20her%20versus%2048%25%20for%20Trump.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInfluential%20Democrats%20including%20U.S.%20Representative%20Jim%20Clyburn%2C%20the%20man%20who%20was%20key%20to%20Biden's%202020%20win%3B%20Rep.%20Gregory%20Meeks%2C%20a%20New%20York%20congressman%20and%20senior%20member%20of%20the%20Congressional%20Black%20Caucus%20and%20Summer%20Lee%2C%20a%20House%20Democrat%20from%20Pennsylvania%20have%20signaled%20Harris%20would%20be%20the%20best%20option%20to%20lead%20the%20ticket%20if%20Biden%20chooses%20to%20step%20aside.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHouse%20Minority%20Leader%20Hakeem%20Jeffries%20has%20also%20privately%20signaled%20the%20same%20to%20lawmakers%2C%20a%20Congressional%20aide%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHarris%20is%20taken%20so%20seriously%2C%20two%20Republican%20donors%20told%20Reuters%20they%20would%20prefer%20for%20Trump%20to%20face%20Biden%20than%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20would%20prefer%20Biden%20to%20stay%20in%20place%26quot%3B%20rather%20than%20be%20replaced%20by%20Harris%2C%20said%20Pauline%20Lee%2C%20a%20fundraiser%20for%20Trump%20in%20Nevada%20after%20the%20June%2027%20debate%2C%20who%20said%20she%20thought%20Biden%20had%20proved%20himself%20to%20be%20%26quot%3Bincompetent.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnd%20some%20on%20Wall%20Street%2C%20an%20important%20Democratic%20fundraising%20center%2C%20are%20starting%20to%20indicate%20a%20preference.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BBiden%20is%20already%20behind%20Trump%2C%20and%20is%20unlikely%20to%20be%20able%20to%20overcome%20that%20gap%20given%20where%20his%20campaign%20is%20currently.%20Having%20VP%20Harris%20likely%20improves%20Democrats'%20odds%20of%20taking%20the%20White%20House%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Sonu%20Varghese%2C%20global%20macro%20strategist%20at%20Carson%20Group%2C%20a%20financial%20services%20company%2C%20after%20the%20debate.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20potentially%20more%20upside%20for%20her%20chances%20than%20Biden's%20at%20this%20point.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20majority%20of%20Americans%20see%20Harris%20in%20a%20negative%20light%2C%20as%20they%20do%20both%20men%20running%20for%20president.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPolling%20outlet%20Five%20Thirty%20Eight%20said%2037.1%25%20of%20voters%20approve%20of%20Harris%20and%2049.6%25%20disapprove.%20Those%20numbers%20compare%20to%2036.9%25%20and%2057.1%25%20for%20Biden%2C%20and%2038.6%25%20and%2053.6%25%20for%20Trump.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EWomen%2C%20Black%20Voters%2C%20Gaza%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20repealed%20women's%20constitutional%20right%20to%20abortion%20in%202022%2C%20Harris%20has%20become%20the%20Biden%20administration's%20foremost%20voice%20on%20reproductive%20rights%2C%20an%20issue%20Democrats%20are%20betting%20on%20to%20help%20them%20win%20the%202024%20election.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20Democrats%20believe%20Harris%20could%20energize%20Democratic-leaning%20groups%20whose%20enthusiasm%20for%20Biden%20has%20faded%2C%20including%20Black%20voters%2C%20young%20voters%20and%20those%20who%20do%20not%20approve%20of%20Biden's%20handling%20of%20the%20Israel-Hamas%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BShe%20would%20energize%20the%20Black%2C%20brown%2C%20and%20Asian%20Pacific%20members%20of%20our%20coalition...she%20would%20immediately%20pull%20the%20dispirited%20youth%20of%20our%20country%20back%20into%20the%20fold%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Tim%20Ryan%2C%20a%20former%20Democratic%20Congressman%20from%20Ohio%2C%20in%20a%20recent%20op-ed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDemocratic%20and%20Republican%20suburban%20women%20may%20also%20be%20more%20comfortable%20with%20her%20then%20Trump%20or%20Biden%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20vice%20president%2C%20Harris's%20public%20Israel%20strategy%20is%20identical%20to%20Biden's%2C%20although%20she%20was%20the%20first%20senior%20leader%20of%20the%20U.S.%20government%20to%20call%20for%20a%20ceasefire%20in%20March.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSimply%20swapping%20out%20the%20candidate%20does%20not%20address%20the%20central%20concern%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20movement%2C%20said%20Abbas%20Alawieh%2C%20a%20member%20of%20the%20national%20%26quot%3BUncommitted%26quot%3B%20movement%20that%20withheld%20votes%20for%20Biden%20in%20the%20primary%20based%20on%20his%20support%20of%20Israel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20Biden%20were%20to%20step%20aside%2C%20there%20could%20be%20a%20competition%20between%20other%20Democrats%20to%20become%20the%20nominee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20party%20were%20then%20to%20choose%20another%20candidate%20over%20Harris%2C%20some%20Democrats%20say%20it%20could%20lose%20the%20support%20of%20many%20Black%20voters%20who%20were%20critical%20to%20Biden's%20election%20win%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThere%20is%20no%20alternative%20besides%20Kamala%20Harris%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Adrianne%20Shropshire%2C%20executive%20director%20of%20Black%20voter%20outreach%20group%20BlackPAC.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20the%20Democratic%20Party%20thinks%20that%20they%20have%20problems%20now%20with%20their%20base%20being%20confused...%20Jump%20over%20the%20Black%20woman%2C%20the%20vice%20president%2C%20and%20I%20don't%20think%20the%20Democratic%20Party%20actually%20recovers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EToo%20Lefty%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Harris%20may%20struggle%20to%20reel%20in%20moderate%20Democrats%20and%20the%20independent%20voters%20who%20like%20Biden's%20centrist%20policies%2C%20some%20Democratic%20donors%20said.%20Both%20parties%20seek%20independents%20to%20help%20pull%20them%20over%20the%20finishing%20line%20in%20presidential%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BHer%20greatest%20weakness%20is%20that%20her%20public%20brand%20has%20been%20associated%20with%20the%20far%20left%20wing%20of%20the%20Democratic%20Party%20...%20and%20the%20left%20wing%20of%20the%20Democratic%20party%20cannot%20win%20a%20national%20election%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dmitri%20Mehlhorn%2C%20a%20fundraiser%20and%20adviser%20to%20LinkedIn%20co-founder%20and%20Democratic%20megadonor%20Reid%20Hoffman.%20%26quot%3BThat%20is%20the%20challenge%20that%20she%20will%20have%20to%20overcome%20if%20she%20is%20the%20nominee.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHarris%20would%20take%20over%20money%20raised%20by%20the%20Biden%20campaign%20and%20inherit%20campaign%20infrastructure%2C%20a%20critical%20advantage%20with%20just%20four%20months%20before%20election%20day%20on%20Nov.%205.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20any%20Democratic%20campaign%20still%20needs%20to%20raise%20hundreds%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%20more%20before%20November%20to%20be%20successful%2C%20strategists%20say.%20And%20there%2C%20Harris%20could%20be%20a%20liability.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20can%20tell%20you%20we%20have%20a%20really%20tough%20time%20raising%20money%20for%20her%26quot%3B%20said%20a%20source%20at%20the%20Democratic%20National%20Committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20presidential%20candidate%20ahead%20of%20the%202020%20election%2C%20Harris%20lagged%20Biden%20in%20raising%20money.%20She%20dropped%20out%20of%20the%20race%20in%20December%202019%2C%20the%20same%20month%20her%20campaign%20reported%20%2439.3%20million%20in%20total%20contributions.%20Biden's%20campaign%20reported%20%2460.9%20million%20in%20the%20same%20period.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Biden's%20campaign%20raised%20a%20record%20%2448%20million%20in%20the%2024%20hours%20after%20he%20named%20Harris%20as%20his%20running%20mate%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHarris's%20prosecutorial%20background%20could%20shine%20in%20a%20head-to-head%20debate%20against%20Trump%2C%20some%20Democrats%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BShe%20is%20incredibly%20focused%20and%20forceful%20and%20smart%2C%20and%20if%20she%20prosecutes%20the%20case%20against%20the%20criminality%20of%20Donald%20Trump%2C%20she%20will%20rip%20him%20apart%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Mehlhorn.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERepublican%20attacks%20on%20Harris%20are%20ramping%20up%20as%20she%20has%20been%20floated%20as%20a%20possible%20Biden%20replacement.%20Conservative%20talking%20heads%20are%20re-circulating%20criticism%20leveled%20at%20her%20during%20the%202020%20race%2C%20including%20from%20some%20Democrats%2C%20that%20Harris%20laughs%20too%20much%2C%20that%20she%20is%20untested%2C%20and%20unqualified.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKelly%20Dittmar%2C%20a%20political%20science%20professor%20at%20Rutgers%20University%2C%20said%20the%20attacks%20are%20part%20of%20a%20long%20history%20of%20objectifying%20and%20denigrating%20women%20of%20color%20in%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BUnfortunately%20the%20reliance%20on%20both%20racist%20and%20sexist%20attacks%20and%20tropes%20against%20women%20running%20for%20office%20is%20historically%20common%20and%20persists%20to%20this%20day%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dittmar.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E